{"cursor":"3915","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox astronaut |image = |othername =Muhammed Ahmed Faris |type =Interkosmos\nResearch Cosmonaut |nationality =Syrian |status =Retired |birth_date =\n|birth_place =Aleppo, Syria |date_death = |death_place = |occupation =Pilot\n|rank =General, Syrian Air Force |selection =1985 Intercosmos Group\n|time =7d 23h 04m |mission =Mir EP-1 (Soyuz TM-3 / Soyuz TM-2) |insignia =\n|awards = }}\n\n'Muhammed Ahmed Faris' (; born 26 May 1951) is a Syrian military aviator. He was\nthe first Syrian and the second Arab in space.\n\nBorn in Aleppo, Syria, he was a pilot in the Syrian Air Force with the rank of a\ncolonel. He specialized in navigation when he was selected to participate in the\nIntercosmos spaceflight program on 30 September 1985.\n\nHe flew as Research Cosmonaut in the Interkosmos program on Soyuz TM-3 to the\nMir space station in July 1987, spending 7 days 23 hours and 5 minutes in space.\nHe returned to Earth aboard Soyuz TM-2.\n\nMuhammed Faris was awarded the title Hero of the Soviet Union on 30 July 1987.\nHe was also awarded the Order of Lenin.\n[http://www.warheroes.ru/hero/hero.asp?Hero_id=2298 Biography] at the website on\nHeroes of the Soviet Union and Russia\n\nAfter his spaceflight, he returned to the Syrian Air Force and lived in Aleppo.\nHe is married and has three children.\n\nOn 4 August 2012, during the Syrian civil war, he defected from and joined the\narmed opposition. [http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jAEKtby9Ymk\nØ±Ø§Ø¦Ø¯ Ø§ÙÙØ¶Ø§Ø¡ Ø§ÙÙÙØ§Ø¡ ÙØ­ÙØ¯ ÙØ§Ø±Ø³ ÙØ¹ÙÙ Ø§ÙØ´ÙØ§ÙÙ]\n\nOn 13 September 2012, made an exclusive interview with Al Aan TV and covered\nmany topics regarding the Syrian civil war.\n","linknr":183,"url":"Muhammed_Faris","recorded":1375077995,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Muhammed_Faris&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Muhammed_Faris&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?act